SUMMARY:Meet-The-Author: Medinay Bawudun\, Rise Up My Uyghurs
DESCRIPTION:Medinay Bawudun has spent 26 years away from her homeland\, y
 et she continues to stand proudly for Uyghur culture. Through her poetry 
 and music\, she shares the stories\, struggles\, and resilient spirit of 
 her people with audiences around the world. For 17 years\, she worked as 
 a journalist at ├£r├╝mqi TV and Radio Free Asia\, exploring themes of ide
 ntity\, homeand social awareness\, and her dual perspective as both journ
 alist and poet allows her to reflect the Uyghur experience with honesty\,
  sensitivity\, and depth. Collaborating with artists across Central Asia 
 and creating powerful songs like "Rise Up My Uyghurs" and "The Way Back H
 ome"\, Bawudun has become a heartfelt and inspiring voice for the Uyghur 
 diaspora. As the founder of the Uyghur Culture Heritage Project\, she tir
 elessly works to preserve and share Uyghur traditions\, using her poetry 
 and music to build a bridge that invites listeners to feel\, connect\, an
 d celebrate the enduring spirit of Uyghur culture.&#160\;  Co-sponsored b
 y Bloomington's own Marco &amp\; Polo Uyghur and Eurasian restaurant\, in
  consortium with the Center for the Languages of the Central Asian Region
 .&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Medinay Bawudun has spent 26 years away
  from her homeland\, yet she continues to stand proudly for Uyghur cultur
 e. Through her poetry and music\, she shares the stories\, struggles\, an
 d resilient spirit of her people with audiences around the world. For 17 
 years\, she worked as a journalist at ├£r├╝mqi TV and Radio Free Asia\, e
 xploring themes of identity\, homeand social awareness\, and her dual per
 spective as both journalist and poet allows her to reflect the Uyghur exp
 erience with honesty\, sensitivity\, and depth. Collaborating with artist
 s across Central Asia and creating powerful songs like "Rise Up My Uyghur
 s" and "The Way Back Home"\, Bawudun has become a heartfelt and inspiring
  voice for the Uyghur diaspora. As the founder of the Uyghur Culture Heri
 tage Project\, she tirelessly works to preserve and share Uyghur traditio
 ns\, using her poetry and music to build a bridge that invites listeners 
 to feel\, connect\, and celebrate the enduring spirit of Uyghur culture.&
 #160\;<br /><br />  Co-sponsored by Bloomington's own Marco &amp\; Polo U
 yghur and Eurasian restaurant\, in consortium with the Center for the Lan
 guages of the Central Asian Region.&#160\;</p>
