SUMMARY:"Global\, Sustainable\, Digital: How Entrepreneurs Change the Wor
 ld?" with Magdalena Marczewska
DESCRIPTION:This seminar explores how startups expand globally in a digit
 al and sustainability-focused world. Many new companies reach internation
 al customers from day one using online platforms and digital tools. The t
 alk explains how entrepreneurs combine technology\, global opportunities\
 , and responsible business practices to grow their ventures and compete i
 n today's rapidly changing economy.Magdalena Marczewska is a Senior Resea
 rch Fellow and Ko┼øciuszko Foundation Fellow at Indiana University and a 
 faculty member at the University of Warsaw. Her research focuses on innov
 ation\, technology management\, and digital transformation. Combining aca
 demic and industry experience\, she works as an Innovation Coach supporti
 ng startups and leads international research projects on entrepreneurship
 \, sustainable business\, and strategy.Sponsored by the Polish Studies Ce
 nter
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><span style="font-family: 'Segoe UI'\, 'S
 egoe UI Web (West European)'\, -apple-system\, BlinkMacSystemFont\, Robot
 o\, 'Helvetica Neue'\, sans-serif\; font-size: 15px\; color: #242424\;" d
 ata-olk-copy-source="MessageBody">This seminar explores how startups expa
 nd globally in a digital and sustainability-focused world. Many new compa
 nies reach international customers from day one using online platforms an
 d digital tools. The talk explains how entrepreneurs combine technology\,
  global opportunities\, and responsible business practices to grow their 
 ventures and compete in today's rapidly changing economy.</span></p><p><s
 pan style="font-family: 'Segoe UI'\, 'Segoe UI Web (West European)'\, -ap
 ple-system\, BlinkMacSystemFont\, Roboto\, 'Helvetica Neue'\, sans-serif\
 ; font-size: 15px\; color: #242424\;" data-olk-copy-source="MessageBody">
 Magdalena Marczewska is a Senior Research Fellow and Ko┼øciuszko Foundati
 on Fellow at Indiana University and a faculty member at the University of
  Warsaw. Her research focuses on innovation\, technology management\, and
  digital transformation. Combining academic and industry experience\, she
  works as an Innovation Coach supporting startups and leads international
  research projects on entrepreneurship\, sustainable business\, and strat
 egy.</span></p><p><span style="font-family: 'Segoe UI'\, 'Segoe UI Web (W
 est European)'\, -apple-system\, BlinkMacSystemFont\, Roboto\, 'Helvetica
