SUMMARY:Walking as Inquiry Summit
DESCRIPTION:Join colleagues for an exploratory afternoon of walking\, thi
 nking\, community-building\, and conversation at Bradford Woods.  The sum
 mit will feature guided walks\, brief presentations on walking methodolog
 ies\, collaborative discussions about the role of embodied movement and p
 lace in arts and humanities research\, and an introduction to new grants 
 for ambulatory research and creative practice. We will move between outdo
 or immersion and indoor reflection\, creating space for both embodied pra
 ctice and critical dialogue about who walks\, where\, when\, and why.&#16
 0\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Join colleagues for an exploratory afte
 rnoon of walking\, thinking\, community-building\, and conversation at Br
 adford Woods.</p><p>  The summit will feature guided walks\, brief presen
 tations on walking methodologies\, collaborative discussions about the ro
 le of embodied movement and place in arts and humanities research\, and a
 n introduction to new grants for ambulatory research and creative practic
 e. We will move between outdoor immersion and indoor reflection\, creatin
 g space for both embodied practice and critical dialogue about who walks\
 , where\, when\, and why.&#160\;</p>
