DESCRIPTION:Bio  Mahdi Taraghi is a third-year Ph.D. student in Environme
 ntal Science at the O'Neill School of Public and Environmental Affairs\, 
 Indiana University Bloomington. He holds a Master's degree in Water Resou
 rces Engineering and is passionate about the intersection of environmenta
 l policy\, socio-environmental systems\, and complex systems modeling. Hi
 s research focuses on the dynamic interplay between human decision-making
  and environmental processes\, using agent-based modeling to investigate 
 complex interactions within socio-environmental systems.About the Ostrom 
 Workshop Research Series  Learn about innovative research by Graduate Stu
 dents and Visiting Scholars as they advance the mission of the Ostrom Wor
 kshop\, building upon the theme of governance to understand and address m
 ajor societal problems.
