LOCATION:GISB - Room Number: 1060
SUMMARY:Workshop on Measuring International Development\, Advancing Equity
DESCRIPTION:Humanity stands at a crossroads. While we have made incredibl
 e strides in human development\, we also face existential threatsŌĆöfrom 
 climate change and pandemics to growing polarization and inequality. To o
 vercome these threats\, we must work together to advance a coherent visio
 n of human development centered on guaranteeing every person a dignified\
 , or at least minimally good\, life. This workshop addresses the conceptu
 al and practical gaps in how we measure social progress. A narrow focus o
 n GDP is no longer sufficient\; it is distribution-insensitive and fails 
 to capture the non-market values essential for mutual flourishing. This w
 orkshop will explore how to think about development\, develop better metr
 ics\, and put them into practice.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Humanity stands at a crossroads. While 
 we have made incredible strides in human development\, we also face exist
 ential threatsŌĆöfrom climate change and pandemics to growing polarizatio
 n and inequality. To overcome these threats\, we must work together to ad
 vance a coherent vision of human development centered on guaranteeing eve
 ry person a dignified\, or at least minimally good\, life. This workshop 
 addresses the conceptual and practical gaps in how we measure social prog
 ress. A narrow focus on GDP is no longer sufficient\; it is distribution-
 insensitive and fails to capture the non-market values essential for mutu
 al flourishing. This workshop will explore how to think about development
 \, develop better metrics\, and put them into practice.</p>
